      },
      "date": "2013-08-14 00:26:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nIs there anyway we can open a bug with SuSE?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "73c8d7f6e9401fc7f0e8769400afe04e59d59481",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-08-14 15:35:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nKeith: that is a good question.  In theory we should be able to, but not sure we have ever done so for real.  Don't have good visibility into their bug tracking as far as I know.  Suspect they already know or at least should know about this one.  The fix has been in upstream attr rpm source for a very long time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f62794a4c4389dd4324fc4c85be68d006bb5a475",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-08-14 18:18:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAs long as it fixed upstream that is fine with me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b67de8ab63317a5a96fe29e243f9010e21147ca0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
